          {
            "text": "A five-minute nighttime tapping practice from Day 27 of a 30-day sleep intensive. The script targets the loneliness that can come with night: the stillness that reads as separation, the quiet that feels like being left behind. The reframe moves toward the specific felt sense that the rest of the living world is also exhaling, and you are part of that.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
